This paper is about developing a detector for anomalous executions in robot-assisted feeding using a long short-term memory based variational autoencoder (LSTM-VAE). The paper focuses on the fusion of high-dimensional and heterogeneous modalities, which is a challenging problem in robotics. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.RO (Robotics). 

The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as LSTM-VAE and anomaly detection, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper uses multimodal sensory signals, which can be processed using computer vision techniques such as cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Finally, the paper evaluates its detector using various metrics, which can be related to sub-category cs.SD (Sound). 

Therefore, the 5 likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely, are cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.SD.
